For use with aftcode it is important to know that:
- The motor scripts respond directly to the position of the ball passed through the /ball_pos topic
- The only files that need to be run on the pi are the motor files found in the motor folder
- 'roslaunch pi_codes foobot.launch' launches all four of the motor scripts in tandem

For use with aftcode2_0 it is import to know that:
- Roscore needs to be running on the master
- tools.py in scripts/libraries contains most of the stepper logic for the low level controllers
- spawn_rod.py requires one argument --rod which for aftcode2_0 can only be either 1 or 2 and instantiates one instance of velocity_ctrl.py each for the angular and linear directions of the specified rod
- The low level controller recieves commands from the /omega_d geometry twist topic where the angular channels represent the angular motors and the linear channels represent the linear motors

Note: If you were to expand the number of motors on the table you would need to abide by the numbering scheme found in spawn_rod.py and velocity_ctrl.py that assume the farthest left rod on the hardware side
is actuated by motors 1 and 2 where 1 is the linear direction and 2 is the angular; rod 2 would have motors 3, linear, and 4, angular, and so on.

Note: C++ codes have very little benefit here. The timing delay problems caused by the python scripts can be fixed by a constant timing offset value. The files found in src can be largely ignored.
